HEADWORD: Flota
<hw>Flo"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. See
<er>Flotilla</er>.]</ety> <def>A fleet; especially, a fleet of Spanish
ships which formerly sailed every year from Cadiz to Vera Cruz, in
Mexico, to transport to Spain the production of Spanish
America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flotage</ent>⟦br⟧
